==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Smilax
<hw>Smi"lax</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L., bindweed, Gr.
<?/<?/<?/.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>A genus of
perennial climbing plants, usually with a prickly woody stem; green
brier, or cat brier. The rootstocks of certain species are the source of
the medicine called sarsaparilla.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>A delicate
trailing plant (<spn>Myrsiphyllum asparagoides</spn>) much used for
decoration. It is a native of the Cape of Good Hope.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Smile</ent>⟦br⟧
